quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  33,59,"O Prophet! Tell your wives and your daughters and the women of the faithful to draw closely over themselves their chadors [when going out]. That makes it likely for them to be recognized and not be troubled, and Allah is all-forgiving, all-merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a sickness, and the rumourmongers in the city do not desist, We will prompt you [to take action] against them; then they will not be your neighbours in it except briefly"
  33,61,"Accursed, they will be seized wherever they are confronted and slain violently"
  33,62,"Allah’s precedent with those who passed away before, and you will never find any change in Allah’s precedent"
  33,63,"The people question you concerning the Hour. Say, ‘Its knowledge is only with Allah.’ What do you know, maybe the Hour is near"
  33,64,Indeed Allah has cursed the faithless and prepared for them a blaze
  33,65,"in which they will remain forever, and will not find any guardian or helper"
  33,66,"The day when their faces are turned about in the Fire, they will say, ‘We wish we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Apostle!’"
  33,67,"They will say, ‘Our Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elders, and they led us astray from the way.’"
  33,68,Our Lord! Give them a double punishment and curse them with a mighty curse.’